Definitions:

container-url 
    A properly formatted URL which identifies the machine on which the to be attached container is running.
    The URL should end in '/axis/services/VCGRContainerPortType'. 

hosting-environment-rns-path 
    A valid local file-system path which specifies the name the attached container is to be called in the new hosting environment. 

Description:

The attach-host tool allows a user to attach a container into a different hosting environment.
The container is specified by the container-url.
The name of the container in the new hosting environment is specified by hosting-environment-rns-path.
